Detailed Description

This file contains the implementation of the APIs present in the device abstraction layer file of TESOC.

static int32_t TesocDomainStart ( uint32_t  baseAddr,
uint32_t  domainLabel 
)
static

This function is used to enable TESOC test on selected domain by writing enable pattern to TESOC domain enable register for that domain.

Parameters
baseAddrBase Address of the TESOC Registers.
domainLabelDomain on which test is run. Refer enum #tesocDomainLabel_t for details.
Returns
status Whether TESOC test start on domain succeeded. STW_SOK : Success STW_EFAIL : Failure
static int32_t TesocGetDiagSliceNumber ( uint32_t  baseAddr,
uint32_t  testId 
)
static

This function will return diagnostic slice number for domain.

Parameters
baseAddrBase Address of the TESOC Registers.
testIdTESOC Test ID.
Returns
diagSliceNumber Whether diagnostic slice number for domain fetched correctly. (+ve value) : diagnostic slice number. (-1) : No diagnostic slice for this domain.
static int32_t TesocGetTestSliceResult ( uint32_t  baseAddr,
uint32_t  domainLabel,
uint32_t *  testSliceResult 
)
static

This function is used to read TESOC slice result register for domain on which test was run. Slice result can be fail, pass(or not run) depending on slice configuration for test.

Parameters
baseAddrBase Address of the TESOC Registers.
domainLabelDomain on which test is run. Refer enum #tesocDomainLabel_t for details.
testSliceResultPointer to array of size NUM_SLICE_BLOCKS for storing slice result.
Returns
status Whether slice result info is fetched correctly. STW_SOK : Success. STW_EFAIL : Failure.
